<@U5LSFM0JJ> Confirming you're looking for the least common multiple between the two inputs. I'm not sure what your methodology is, but here's one possible way of doing it.  Let's call the variable for the solution "LCM". You know that LCM must be some integer (i) times one of the inputs (say input1). For example, if your input input1 is 5, you know the LCM must be 5,10,15,20,25... or so on (not sure which one yet, bu it has to be one of those). You also know that LCM must be divisible by input2.  I hope this can put you on the right path. Good luck!

file.title: Opening IPython Notebook: execution error: doesn’t understand the “open location” message. (-1708)
file.preview:
To open the Jupyter/IPython notebook, type jupyter notebook or ipython notebook from the Mac Terminal prompt (i.e. the command line).

If you get the error in the title above, find the file ~/.jupyter/jupyter_notebook_config.py and edit the line:

c.NotebookApp.browser = u'chrome'

Change chrome to Safari if you use Safari instead.
